I"Z<p>The PhD news: Year four is underway. I’m currently recruiting for an interview/data collection study involving <a href="https://whilab.org/projects/bd-finhealth.html">money behaviors and bipolar disorder</a>. We’re aiming to design personalized, privacy-preserving, supportive financial technologies tailored to this illness.</p>

<p>I’ll be traveling to Japan for <a href="https://chi2025.acm.org/">CHI 2025</a> where I’m co-organizing a workshop <a href="https://chi2025.acm.org/for-authors/workshops/accepted-workshops/#w3">The Future of Money and HCI</a>.</p>

<p>I’m really enjoying reading <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ways_of_Seeing">Ways of Seeing</a> by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Berger">John Berger</a>. I’m also excited for <a href="https://shop.serpentinegalleries.org/products/holly-herndon-mat-dryhurst-all-media-is-training-data">All Media is Training Data</a> by <a href="https://herndondryhurst.studio/">Holly Herndon &amp; Mat Dryhurst</a>.</p>

